================================================================================
📄 FILE AND FOLDER ROLES
================================================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. CORE SOURCE FILES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* main.js
  - Purpose: Electron main process controller.
  - Role: Manages transparent window lifecycle (`transparent: true`, `alwaysOnTop: true`),
    IPC handlers (`resize-window`, `set-ignore-mouse`, `get-diagnostic-logs`, `clear-diagnostic-logs`),
    Steamworks SDK integration (`@skyatnpm/steamworks-js` with `MockSteamClient` fallback),
    20-minute background uptime monitor for achievement `ACH_TRAVEL_FAR`, cursor boundary edge
    polling (`edgeCheckInterval`, 100ms), and centralized file diagnostic logging (`logDiagnostic`).

* renderer.js
  - Purpose: Frontend WebGL engine and user interaction manager.
  - Role: Initializes Three.js WebGL renderer, scene, lights, and cameras. Operates the 60 FPS
    render loop (bobbing, 3-axis rotation, animation mixers). Handles Blender-style 3D viewport controls
    (Orbit, Pan, Zoom, Orthographic views), drag-and-drop `.glb` model loading, raycasting hover hit-tests,
    View-Only mode (`Ctrl + V`), async background thumbnail generation (`.previews/`), settings saving,
    and system diagnostic event triggers.

* i18nManager.js
  - Purpose: Multi-language internationalization engine.
  - Role: Wraps `i18next` framework logic. Defines `SUPPORTED_LANGUAGES` array (31 languages),
    detects initial OS/system language (`navigator.language`), dynamically loads translation resources
    from `locales/<code >/translation.json`, and updates all DOM elements bearing `data-i18n` and
    `data-i18n-title` attributes upon language change.

* index.html
  - Purpose: Document viewport container.
  - Role: Hosts the Three.js canvas container, settings gear toggle, glassmorphic Settings Panel,
    Language Selector dropdown (31 options), mascot preview thumbnail grid, viewport control guide,
    and Diagnostics Console. Uses ESM script tags and importmaps.

* style.css
  - Purpose: Application stylesheet.
  - Role: Enforces absolute background transparency across the HTML canvas, styling for glassmorphic
    settings overlays, custom scrollbars, range sliders, and cross-platform font stacks (`PingFang SC`,
    `Hiragino Sans`, `Meiryo`, `Malgun Gothic`, `Noto Sans CJK`).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. CONFIGURATION AND PACKAGING
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* package.json
  - Purpose: Node manifest file.
  - Role: Configures dependencies (`three`, `i18next`, `@skyatnpm/steamworks-js`, `electron-packager`)
    and script commands (`npm start`, `npm run build`).

* package-lock.json
  - Purpose: Dependency lock file.
  - Role: Locks exact dependency tree versions installed by npm.

* steam_appid.txt
  - Purpose: Steam App ID definition.
  - Role: Specifies `480` (Spacewar testing ID) for local Steamworks SDK connection.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. DIRECTORIES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* assets/
  - Purpose: Zero-code custom model directory and runtime storage.
  - Role: Contains custom `.glb` / `.gltf` assets, the generated thumbnail cache (`.previews/`),
    the `settings` config file, and `diagnostics.log`.

* locales/
  - Purpose: Internationalization resource dictionaries.
  - Role: Contains 31 subdirectories each housing a `translation.json` file for localizing all UI elements.

* DesktopPet-win32-x64/
  - Purpose: Standalone compiled distribution package.
  - Role: Portable Windows build directory containing `DesktopPet.exe` and bundled binaries.
